<item>
 <title>DOE Proposes Requirement for Certification of Admissibility for Covered Products and Equipment</title>
 <link>https://energy.gov/gc/articles/doe-proposes-requirement-certification-admissibility-covered-products-and-equipment</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div  property=&quot;content:encoded&quot; class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt; &lt;p&gt;DOE has issued a &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.regulations.gov/#!documentDetail;D=EERE-2015-BT-CE-0019-0001&quot;&gt;Notice of Proposed Rulemaking &lt;/a&gt;(NOPR) in which it proposes to require that a person importing into the United States any covered product or equipment subject to an applicable energy conservation standard provide, prior to importation, a certification of admissibility to the DOE for the covered product or equipment.  The certification would be submitted to DOE through the U.S. Customs and Border Protection’s Automated Commercial Environment (ACE).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
 <pubDate>Mon, 22 Feb 2016 23:26:00 +0000</pubDate>
 <dc:creator />
